  "title": "Western Cuisine Chef(CBD area)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Vacancy: Chef (Western Cuisine)</h3><h3>Industry: Food & Beverage / Catering</h3><h3>Work Location: Raffles Place / Bayfront, Singapore</h3><p>⸻</p><h3>Salary</h3><p>SGD 5,000</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Working Hours</h3><p>Working Schedule: Monday to Saturday 11:00am to 12:00am</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Monthly Rest Days</h3><p>6 days</p><p>⸻</p><h3>About the Company</h3><p><u>The employer is a </u><u><strong>catering and bar company</strong></u><u> operating within the food and beverage sector, offering Western cuisine and dining services in a fast-paced hospitality environment.</u></p><p>⸻</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Prepare, cook, and present Western cuisine with a focus on taste, quality, and presentation</p></li><li><p>Manage kitchen operations, including staff scheduling and work allocation</p></li><li><p>Handle supplier ordering and conduct monthly inventory checks</p></li><li><p>Calculate and monitor food costs</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with food safety and hygiene standards</p></li><li><p>Manage kitchen operations during peak hours to ensure smooth workflow</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with the kitchen team to maintain efficiency and consistency</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Proven experience as a <strong>Western cuisine chef</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge and practical skills in Western cooking techniques</p></li><li><p>Ability to work efficiently in a fast-paced kitchen environment</p></li><li><p>Good teamwork, coordination, and organisational skills</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail and quality standards</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Benefits</h3><p>Employment terms and benefits in accordance with Ministry of Manpower (MOM) regulations</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Contract</h3><p>Not specified</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Interview Method</h3><p>Video interview or On-site interview</p>",
